node.text:
🧠 Mondays can be hard. Let’s check-in.

👇 Comment an emoji below, which affirmation do you need for the week? ✨

🕷- You are not your anxious thoughts.
🪲- You have survived 100% of your worst days. 
🦋 - You are Good Enough.
🐞- What if it all works out? 
🐛 - Give Yourself Time. 
🐜 - Small steps are big steps

Responding to someone else in the comments with some love and kindness is encouraged 💗

#community

💕✨😊🙏

♥️ If you need support in a challenging time:

What you are experiencing can really impact your mental health and ability to focus. We wanted to include some resources of where you can reach out for support if it ever feels quite challenging. 🙏

All US residents can Text HOME to 741741 Crisis Text Line is available 24/7 to connect you with a trained crisis counselor ready to help you through any situation you’re finding challenging. This can range from school stress to coronavirus anxiety, depression to suicidal thoughts, and everything in between. A safe and confidential platform, Crisis Text Line can help you through your most difficult moments.

To find more resources (including inside or outside of the USA) check out our Mental Health Resources on our website. ♥️🙏 It’s okay to ask for help, you are not alone!!

Sending you all so much love ♥️🌈

🌈 GOING TO THERAPY IS COOL IS BACK 😊🌈

Therapy builds resilience and it becomes a place to acknowledge how much strength it took to grow through what you have experienced in your life. ⛅️

Therapy, as a self-care practice, has the ability to save lives. It's a brave space to notice, recognize, and let go of judgement alongside a trained professional who will navigate the healing journey with you. 🌞

So, yeah... I guess you can tell that we think therapy is pretty cool. 

If you do too, we'd love for you to pick up one of these for yourself or a loved one who thinks therapy is pretty cool too 🌈

Have you ever tried therapy? Comment below! 👇👇👇

( 🎨 on hoodie by @crystaldrawsstuff )

Gentle reminder for you 💓 Hope you get to rest and recharge tonight. Rest is such an essential part of self-care🌙

Comment below, have you been getting enough rest lately?

( 🎨 by @littlearthlings )

1 MILLION FOLLOWERS?! We are floored. 😱

🎊 1 million means that 1 million humans have been drawn to the work, energy, and intention we've put into this page. 

For this, we thank you from the bottom of our hearts and send you so much love 💓

Simply, we are you. We have relationships with anxiety, depression, and burnout... all of which show up in moments such as these where we second guess and hesitate to love ourselves as is and to show up as we are... imperfect humans who are trying to do good and hoping that it's okay to take up some room in this world. 

🙏 We are one of you, the million humans advocating for mental health because shame and stigma are too heavy to carry and everyone is deserving of a supportive community that is there to remind them of their wonderfulness. 

At the core of @ selfcareisforeveryone is a small family with immigrant roots and a shared desire to heal generational wounds that continue to keep us feeling disconnected and invisible. 

We also wanted to share in this moment of celebration with our entire team. May this post serve as an opportunity for you all to see all the lovely faces of the hardworking humans behind this account, brand, and company that dedicate a large number of the hours in their days and weeks to keep this project alive and in service of this wonderful, empathetic, and kind community.

Thank you to anyone who has ever supported us in this mission. We look forward to continuing to serve this community and help raise money for suicide prevention, spread awareness and normalize conversations around mental health. 🦋

Drop some 🎉🎊 if you’ve been on this journey with us and want to help us celebrate. THANK YOU. ✨

node.text:
Do you find yourself wanting to close up and hide when you are feeling vulnerable? 🥺 You are not alone in this. 

🦋 Here’s the story behind this beautiful art from the artist @bigfightinwords :

“A good friend told me about this butterfly that camouflages itself to avoid predation. When I saw it I thought it was too beautiful to ever shut its wings.

But folding up serves a very important function- protection.
This butterfly will close its wings until it is safe enough to open up again.
-

We all have to become this butterfly at some point in our lives...

Folding away our color and disguising ourselves so we are not easy targets- it’s a normal and integral part of learning to survive.

I think the only thing harder than folding ourselves away, is learning to open up again.

There is nothing easy about opening our wings after we have been hurt.”

Drop some 🦋🦋🦋 if you’ve felt this way before. 💙

( 🎨 by @bigfightinwords )

Have you ever heard of toxic positivity? 🙏 Sometimes it’s hard to know what to say when someone is opening up about what they are going through. 💔

👆Here are some really helpful examples from @crazyheadcomics of how to respond to better validate someone’s experience. 

👀 While there is good intention when responding with “just stay positive”, this response doesn’t really acknowledge what someone is going through. 

♥️ To help someone feel seen (and heard), save this post for when you may need it and try using some of these responses instead! 

👇Comment below what helps you when you are going through a hard time! 

( 🎨 by @crazyheadcomics )

A much needed Monday reminder 😆

👉 What’s a hard thing you have to do today? Comment below!! 

Feel free to respond to others with anything encouraging! ♥️ 
Let’s hype each other up! 🥰

Ps: it’s the LAST WEEK to receive the FREE month of therapy that comes in EVERY order for the rest of August!

🧠 Sunday Mental Health Check-in

👇How have you been speaking with yourself? 

🍄 My inner critic has been loud lately.
🥀 I have been hard on myself
🌻 I have been distracting myself
💐 With curiosity
 🌷With Kindness
🌸 With encouragement 

Responding to someone else in the comments with some love and kindness is encouraged #community 💕✨😊🙏 

♥️ If you need support in a challenging time:

What you are experiencing can really impact your mental health and ability to focus. We wanted to include some resources of where you can reach out for support if it ever feels quite challenging. 🙏

All US residents can Text HOME to 741741 Crisis Text Line is available 24/7 to connect you with a trained crisis counselor ready to help you through any situation you’re finding challenging. This can range from school stress to coronavirus anxiety, depression to suicidal thoughts, and everything in between. A safe and confidential platform, Crisis Text Line can help you through your most difficult moments.

To find more resources (including inside or outside of the USA) check out our Mental Health Resources on our website. ♥️🙏 It’s okay to ask for help, you are not alone!! 

Sending you all so much love ♥️🌈

How do you practice mindfulness? comment below! ♥️

Here are 5️⃣ ways to practice mindfulness before bed or in the morning (or whenever😊) 

1️⃣ Pour yourself a drink of water or tea and drink it really slowly. Be with your drink as you imagine it flowing down your throat and nourishing your body.

2️⃣ Do a body scan to connect with your body. Where do you feel the most tension or discomfort? Sit with your focus directed to this part of yourself, send this area some love and gratitude♥️

3️⃣ Give yourself a hug 🤗 Feel your arms slowly wrap around opposite shoulders. Notice how your touch feels against your skin. 

4️⃣ Listen 🙉 Simply listen to all the sounds you notice happening around you. No need to label the sounds, be with sound ✨

5️⃣ Deep breath’s. Feel your belly / chest rise for five counts and release for 6 counts 😌💨

( 🎨 by @rokaturas )
